---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const title = "Fire Lane Striping Springfield MO | NFPA Compliant Fire Access Markings";
const description = "Fire lane striping and red curb painting in Springfield MO. We connect you with certified contractors for NFPA-compliant fire access markings and emergency vehicle access.";
const h1 = "Fire Lane Striping in Springfield, Missouri";
---

<ServiceLayout {title} {description} {h1}>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-concrete leading-relaxed">
    <p class="text-xl">We connect property managers with certified contractors who specialize in fire lane striping and red curb painting that meets NFPA and local fire code requirements.</p>
    
    <p>Clear, compliant fire lanes are critical for passing inspections and ensuring emergency vehicle access. Many Springfield properties have faded or incorrectly placed fire lanes that need updating.</p>

    <h2>Fire Lane Services</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>NFPA-compliant fire lane layout and striping</li>
      <li>Red curb painting with proper lettering</li>
      <li>Fire hydrant clearance markings</li>
      <li>Emergency vehicle access identification</li>
      <li>Full photographic documentation</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Typical Cost Ranges</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Standard fire lane striping:</strong> $600 – $1,800</li>
      <li><strong>Red curb painting (per 100 linear feet):</strong> $350 – $650</li>
      <li><strong>Full fire lane compliance package:</strong> $1,200 – $3,500</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <h3>How often should fire lanes be repainted?</h3>
    <p>Most commercial properties repaint fire lanes every 18–36 months depending on traffic volume and weather exposure.</p>

    <h3>Will faded fire lanes fail an inspection?</h3>
    <p>Yes. The Springfield Fire Department and insurance inspectors often cite faded or missing fire lane markings.</p>
  </div>

    <h2>Related Service Areas</h2>
    <p>We also serve <a href="/service-area/republic-mo">Republic</a>, <a href="/service-area/nixa-mo">Nixa</a>, <a href="/service-area/ozark-mo">Ozark</a>, <a href="/service-area/battlefield-mo">Battlefield</a>, and <a href="/service-area/rogersville-mo">Rogersville</a>.</p>
</ServiceLayout>